<DOC><DOCNO> AP880227-0069 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-27-88 1108EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Korea-US     02-27 0157</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Korea-US,0162</SECOND><HEAD>US Soldiers Arrive For Major Military Exercises</HEAD><DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A U.S. Navy ship docked in thesouthern port city of Pusan on Saturday and discharged the firstU.S. soldiers and equipment to arrive for large military exercises,news reports said.   The Yonhap news agency said the 26,000-ton Regulus arrived fromTakoma, Wash., carrying 714 U.S. soldiers, 14 helicopters, threetractors and 1,036 trucks.   The United States and South Korea plan to deploy about 200,000soldiers in the annual ``Team Spirit'' exercises, scheduled to runfrom late February to early May.   U.S. officials said the exercises this year will involve about60,000 U.S. military personnel along with U.S. and South Koreanjets, a U.S. aircraft carrier and escorting warships.   About 40,000 U.S. troops from bases in the Pacific and theUnited States are to be brought in to join American troops based inSouth Korea.   North Korea has strongly opposed the exercises.</TEXT></DOC>